#
# iSHELL H-band arc-lamp emission line list for pySpextool wavelength calibration
#
# NASA IRTF iSHELL cross-dispersed echelle spectrograph
# H-band sub-modes (Manual Table 1):
#   H1: orders 311–355, wavelength 1.473–1.683 µm
#   H2: orders 299–388, wavelength 1.544–1.748 µm
#   H3: orders 285–319, wavelength 1.633–1.832 µm
# Arc lamp: ThAr (thorium-argon) — confirmed from Manual Table 1.
# Slit length for H-band modes: 5 arcseconds (Manual Table 1).
#
# NOTE: This file is a placeholder (TBD).  Real line positions, window
#       widths, and fit parameters must be derived from actual iSHELL
#       ThAr arc-lamp spectra.  Consult the NIST Atomic Spectra Database
#       for Th I, Th II, Ar I, and Ar II vacuum wavelengths in the
#       1.47–1.83 µm passband.
#
#=======================================================================================================
#Order   | Vacuum Wavelength   | Species   | Left Window   | Right Window   | Fit Type   | Fit N Terms
#        | (microns)           |           | (Angstroms)   | (Angstroms)    |            |            
#=======================================================================================================
